description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Theatre Scrub Practitioner&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location: Riverside Clinic&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salary: £36000-£40000&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Healthshare is a successful provider of clinical and diagnostic services to the NHS and private sectors across various locations throughout the country. The Day Surgery Clinic has 1 Theatre, 4 Recovery Bays and provides surgery for, General cases, Orthopaedic, Gynecology, Urology. ENT and Plastic Surgery.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As Theatre Scrub Nurse, you will be working in this theatre department, contributing to a safe, efficient and effective perioperative service for patients and consultants users. You will provide support and clinical practice to the operating theatre team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will ensure that you will adhere to professional and national standards following Nursing and Midwifery Council guidelines and recommendations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job Summary&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deliver a consistently high standard of patient care utilising evidence-based practice&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assessing, planning, delivering and evaluation of peri-operative patient care&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare equipment and instruments according to the individual needs of the patient and Surgeon, as well as involvement with the updating of Surgeon preference cards&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure all equipment is checked prior to use and any faults reported to the Theatre Co-ordinator immediately.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare patients and provide assistance for clinical/operative procedures&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate fully as a team member, including working in all areas of the theatre suite, sharing knowledge and information and supporting colleagues, to promote a cohesive team and the achievement of team objectives&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
